\section{Introduction}

% paragraph discussing significance of irrigation to global water use
Irrigation accounts for X\% of water consumption. Irrigation is an essential component of achieving food security. In the future, food production must increase by X\% to meet rising food demand \citep{}. Achieving sustainable agricultural intensification towards this goal is a major challenge. Irrigated land comprises X\% of Earth's cropland but produces Y\% of its total food demand \citep{}. The accurate estimation of irrigation water consumption is an essential requirement of water resources management. \\

% paragraph discussing the basic purpose of irrigation
Irrigation is used to prevent crops from undergoing water stress and thereby to maximise crop yields \citep{}. Water stress begins to occur when the water content of the soil in the root zone falls below field capacity. As a result, the fundamental basis of irrigation water demand esimtation is the calculation of the difference between potential and actual crop evapotranspiration as a function of root zone water content. \\

% one or two paragraphs dicussing current approaches
Irrigation modules of global and regional hydrological models are parameterized using global datasets cropland extent. Models including PCR-GLOBWB... use the MIRCA2000 gridded dataset to define the spatial extent of various crop types. Meanwhile ... use the global cropland dataset of \citet{monfreda2010}. These datasets have a minimum spatial resolution of 5 arcminutes and show the fraction of each grid cell belonging to various crops. In places with more than one growing season per year, this approach fails to represent the sequence of crops on individual fields in the study region. Resolving this discrepancy is an important step towards the inclusion of farm-level water management strategies in global and regional hydrological models. The failure to include these factors means that existing modules fail to account for the feedback between farmer livelihood, irrigation practices and water availability. Furthermore, existing schemes include a limited number of crops. For example, PCR-GLOBWB includes paddy and non-paddy, while ... includes nine crop types. \\

% paragraph to justify the need for a new irrigation module
This paper presents a new irrigation module which resolves these shortcomings. Novel aspects of the irrigation module include:

\begin{itemize}
  \item represents multiple crops and specific crop rotations
  \item explicitly represents the application method (flood, sprinkler, irrigation)
  \item accounts for sub-optimal irrigation and its impact on yield
  \item defines the source of irrigation water, including conjunctive use (i.e. sw/gw)
  \item irrigation cost component which includes informal water markets
\end{itemize}

